headline: J&J results a good sign for market, advisor says
summary: STORY: ASML, the world's biggest supplier of computer chip-making equipment, warned on Wednesday that it may not achieve revenue growth in 2026 as chipmakers building factories in the U.S. await clarity on the potential impact of tariffs."What we've got here is a CEO being brutally honest," says Miller."They really don't know what 2026 is going to look like, so I actually sort of applauded the comment as being so honest in a time when most leaders and most investors are shrugging off the effects of tariffs."Meanwhile, Johnson & Johnson shares surged as it halved its expectations for costs this year related to new tariffs and raised its full-year sales and profit forecast after a strong quarter for flagship cancer drug Darzalex and its cardiovascular devices."This healthcare sector has really been under a cloud for so many reasons, and these stocks have not performed that well. So here's an opportunity to realize you've got probably a value priced leader in the industry responding to some good results and that's what we want to see as this market broadens out."

headline: Johnson & Johnson beats profit estimates on strong Darzalex, medtech sales
summary: (Reuters) -Johnson & Johnson raised its full-year sales forecast on Wednesday after beating estimates for second-quarter profit on strong demand for its cancer drug, Darzalex, and strength in its medical device business.  The company also reduced its expectations for tariff-related costs to $200 million from $400 million for the year, citing the Trump administration's pause on levies on China and other retaliatory tariff measures.  "We were able to absorb that and still raise our EPS guidance by 25 cents on the year," CFO Joseph Wolk said.
